  "description": [
    "TWO HAP LAI H i B hiqilidn T B KrsjMww Jr Hey Mack you want a ride Hey Mack square Hint hat Hey Mack you gotta light I o linin sound familiar Poes it ever bother you to be addressed by this Navy equivalent of the civilians Hey you or Hey Buddy No I guess it doesnt because we get used to this as a part of our kind of life But sometimes it does irritate Just a little doesnt it It seems to add to the feeling of insignifi cance the sense f being nobody in particular Just a number a aid In a record system a billet on the ship Sometimes this makes n mini feel bad and some times it gives a feeling of secur ity depending on the point of view I ciin remember very well that when 1 was a whitehat about 11 years ago 1 found a great deal of comfort in assuring myself that the skipper didnt even know in name To me that meant that I had never been caught that I had never been to mast and that therefore there was no reason for my name to be in the command"
